                            <comment id="431340" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 14:13:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In this interop test case, the client version is 2.15.5, the server version is 2.16.0.RC1, the test is run on the 2.15.5 Lustre clients and&lt;br/&gt;
the test script of the 2.15.5 version will be used to run the test against the server of 2.16.0.RC1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are two options to fix the issue, one is to simply introduce a patch against 2.15.5 (or other old Versions) to fix it, the other is&lt;br/&gt;
a little more complex, to create a patch to add a symlink &quot;least qunit&quot; to the new &quot;least_qunit&quot; for backward compatibility.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431336" author="pjones" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 13:45:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, does that mean there is a defect that will impact users running in interop mode or is it safe to simply introduce a patch to skip the test in interop mode based on when that change was introduced?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431292" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 02:10:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proc entry &quot;lease qunit&quot; in &quot;qmt.lustre-QMT0000.md-0x0.info&quot; had been modified to &quot;least_qunit&quot;  by &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/43099/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/43099/&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14535&quot; title=&quot;add option for LFS to get all quota information&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14535&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14535&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
